  "time_ut": 1656331140,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db6\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0db3\u0dd4\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dbd\u0dd9\u0dc3 \u0db4\u0dcf\u0db4\u0dd0\u0daf\u0dd2 \u0db7\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dba\u0da7 \u0daf\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Encourages the use of bicycles as a solution to the crisis",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Additional Secretary to the Ministry of Transport and Highways, Bernard Wasantha stated that a program has been planned to popularize the use of bicycles not only as a hobby and sport but also as a safe mode of transport among various age groups.",
        "The Additional Secretary said that as a solution to the economic crisis and the fuel crisis facing the country, Ride for Life, the Sri Lanka Cycling Federation, the Institution of Engineers of Sri Lanka, the media, the Sri Lanka Police and various organizations involved in cycling are expected to implement it.",
        "The Additional Secretary made these revelations at a media briefing held today (27) at the Government Information Department Auditorium on \"Promoting the Use of Bicycles as a Safe Transport Model\".",
        "In the face of the current fuel crisis, vehicles have to be kept at home as bicycles have become an essential factor in this era. Chairman Specialist Dr. Amal Harsha de Silva said.",
        "As an introduction to this, the Sri Lanka Institute of Engineers (IESL) and Ride for Life will jointly launch a rally on July 2, 2022 to encourage people to use bicycles from the IESl office in Wijerama, Colombo to Peliyagoda.",
        "Use bicycle headlights at night, have a rear reflector light, have a brake to stop in case of an emergency, have to walk on the left side of the road, wear a light colored suit to easily identify others at night, and have road signs. Walking in obedience, wearing a safety helmet. The Deputy Inspector General of Traffic and Road Safety Indika Hapugoda said that cycling can be done without any accidents if the traffic rules are followed and the road signs are obeyed."
      ],
